Testing out a new snapshot concept to help connective learning while sparring. I started by freezing them mid spar for 5-10 seconds to allow them to evaluate the position, strategy, problems to solve etc. We progressed from pauses to just a verbal queue to “think” which was a queue to take a snapshot of the situation without the pause.

When we started @compoundsportswear I designed everything… I coached @mr_watercooler most his life and he was fresh out of college. Said he wanted to learn how to “design apparel” He’d come in everyday, sit next to me for 5-6 hours and I’d just talk through everything I was doing. He’d take notes, go home, practice and come back the next day. Seeing him so many years later as our teamwear art director & teaching my son @camfretwell the game, is so damn cool. I appreciate you more than you know Turp!

Moved into this empty building with @sfretwell73 & @roper165 13 years ago. Didn’t know how we were gonna pay for it and didn’t really have a clear plan. @compoundsportswear didn’t exist and @compoundwrestling was just getting started. We had good people around us that wanted us to win in life and we woke up each day trying to outwork the world. Not much has changed except we put more stuff inside the building and the one next door. #empiresnotkingdoms
